<plot>Sex, Lies &amp; Superheroes features the writers and artists who have helped make comic books a medium for sophisticated stories and artwork. Stan Lee discusses the origins of the industry; Neil Gaiman and John Byrne speak on superheroes as modern mythology; Frank Miller and Bill Sienkewicz discuss the relationship of politics and comics; Peter David tells the story of the meanest thing he has ever done to a fan; and much more.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?488643</url></doc>
